1
00:00:06,139 --> 00:00:07,139
I'm sorry, Bingchen.

2
00:00:07,640 --> 00:00:08,708
Shasha isn't feeling well.

3
00:00:09,342 --> 00:00:10,342
I can't accept this.

4
00:00:12,712 --> 00:00:14,146
I have an idea.

5
00:00:14,147 --> 00:00:15,315
For this commercial,

6
00:00:15,882 --> 00:00:17,159
why don't we try something bold?

7
00:00:17,183 --> 00:00:18,823
Who says it has to be a straight romance?

8
00:00:19,085 --> 00:00:20,205
What's a "straight romance"?

9
00:00:21,187 --> 00:00:22,521
You know, a guy and a girl.

10
00:00:22,522 --> 00:00:23,689
These days, the internet

11
00:00:23,690 --> 00:00:25,525
is full of BL tropes.

12
00:00:26,192 --> 00:00:27,327
From school stories

13
00:00:27,694 --> 00:00:29,028
to all the hit dramas.

14
00:00:29,562 --> 00:00:30,562
Director Qiao,

15
00:00:30,964 --> 00:00:32,332
you've got to be kidding.

16
00:00:32,632 --> 00:00:33,632
Between who?

17
00:00:34,334 --> 00:00:35,101
Mike?

18
00:00:35,102 --> 00:00:36,436
You're the client, you tell me.

19
00:00:37,737 --> 00:00:38,737
BL

20
00:00:42,375 --> 00:00:43,510
Gets so much engagement.

21
00:00:45,612 --> 00:00:46,612
BL?

22
00:00:46,846 --> 00:00:48,148
That's a bit of a gamble.

23
00:00:49,115 --> 00:00:50,617
My Hei Yan and who?

24
00:00:52,152 --> 00:00:54,354
Or are you planning to recast?

25
00:00:55,188 --> 00:00:56,188
We have them right here.

26
00:00:57,123 --> 00:00:58,358
Hei Yan and Bai Xing.

27
00:00:59,459 --> 00:01:00,459
The two of you?

28
00:01:09,769 --> 00:01:10,770
Those two?

29
00:01:12,605 --> 00:01:13,605
That's ridiculous.

30
00:01:14,307 --> 00:01:15,307
I'm in.

31
00:01:17,310 --> 00:01:18,310
Hei Yan!

32
00:01:18,478 --> 00:01:20,013
Don't start a scene here.

33
00:01:20,413 --> 00:01:22,115
We'll talk about this in private.

34
00:01:23,316 --> 00:01:24,316
Brother,

35
00:01:24,984 --> 00:01:26,224
I'm just following your advice.

36
00:01:26,953 --> 00:01:28,354
Didn't you always tell me

37
00:01:28,621 --> 00:01:29,621
to push the envelope?

38
00:01:29,889 --> 00:01:31,329
What's the point of playing it safe?

39
00:01:32,992 --> 00:01:34,394
Even if you want to try it,

40
00:01:35,195 --> 00:01:36,195
is he

41
00:01:36,329 --> 00:01:37,396
even good enough?

42
00:01:37,397 --> 00:01:38,798
We won't know until we try.

43
00:01:39,365 --> 00:01:40,365
Right, brother?
